  "texts": [
    "This distribution likely stems from the limited performance of the language model used for generation, which restricts ChartQA-M to specific question templates.",
    "In contrast, the human-authored ChartQA-H set features a more diverse distribution, containing (251) data retrieval, (476) visual, (251) compositional, and (272) visual-and-compositional types.",
    "The diversified distribution motivates us to conduct a more comprehensive evaluation of the model's chart understanding ability across different question types, as detailed in the subsequent section.",
    "Impacts of Distribution BiasWe further study how the distribution bias identified in the above section affect the model performance.",
    "Our selected MLLMs include open-source models explicitly trained on ChartQA: LLaVA-1.6-13b [47], LLaVA-1.6-34b [47] and Qwen-VL-Chat [5]; and mainstream commercial models: Qwen-VL-Plus [5], and GPT-4-vision-preview [59]."
